## Review points

- Prefer an ingress-only policy for initial least-privilege learning.
- Keep Service type minimal and avoid unnecessary NodePort exposure.
- Use Ingress TLS for real HTTP exposure.
- cert-manager readiness still requires a controller and issuer at runtime.
- Review egress separately before connecting the application to external services.
- Keep exposure minimal and document every allowed path.
